snippet.textDisplay: Do you know what my honest first reaction was when that Hagi goal went in? My instant response was to look at the ref and linesman to see if it had been ruled out for anything because of the way he'd reffed the game. That's how bad its got now. Your team scoring a perfectly good goal and you're too nervous to celebrate because it could be ruled out. The club need to grow a set of balls and get the SFA investigated for this because you know that lot would. No point in sweeping this under the carpet because we won. I've noticed a trend that the closer we get to the title over the years the worse and most blatant the decisions get against us.
